    <note>Wang(2) Zhengzhong [7078] Zheng(1) Xiu's [7184] father-in-law, Yang(2) Zuo's [2030], grandfather-in-law. Taozhai cang shiji, 39.13a-15b. This funerary inscription is a good example of the collective responsibility of the kindred group: In 1064, The burial of his second wife, surname Lu(5), who died at age 75 in 1063, was handled by his son-in-law, Li(2) Feng [30560], grandson-in-law, Yang(2) Zuo, and sons # 3 and 4, Zongguan [30555] and Zonglin [30556]. At this time, the inscription was drafted by Li Feng's son, Yu [30561] dataset), the caligraphy done by Li(2) Feng's son, Ti [30562], and the seal characters by Zheng(1) Xiu's son, Fangping [12763].</note>
